HEADWORD: Rioter
<hw>Ri"ot*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
riots; a reveler; a roisterer.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One who engages in a riot. See
<er>Riot</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 3.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Riotise</ent>⟦br⟧
